article.description: — Keve Aluma scored 18 points and Virginia Tech held Pittsburgh to a season-low point total en route to a second win over the Panthers in three nights, posting a 74-47 victory on Monday night.
article.headline: Aluma leads Virginia Tech to a 74-47 rout of Pittsburgh
article.linkText: Aluma leads Virginia Tech to a 74-47 rout of Pittsburgh
article.story: BLACKSBURG, Va. -- — Keve Aluma scored 18 points and Virginia Tech held Pittsburgh to a season-low point total en route to a second win over the Panthers in three nights, posting a 74-47 victory on Monday night. The Hokies have won four straight games, and play their next three games at home. Pittsburgh lost for the fourth straight time. Mouhamadou Gueye hit a 3-pointer two minutes into the game and John Hugley followed with a layup to give Pitt a 5-0 lead, but Virginia Tech answered with 17 straight points and held a 35-17 lead at intermission. Virginia Tech was 13 of 27 from 3-point range and six players knocked down at least two 3s. Nahiem Alleyne led the way from distance, hitting 3 of 5 and scored 11 points. Aluma was 2 of 3 from deep and grabbed six rebounds. Hunter Cattoor added 12 points and six boards. Femi Odukale led the Panthers with 16 points and four assists. Gueye was 5 of 7 from 3-point range and totaled 15 points. The Hokies (14-10, 6-7 Atlantic Coast) play host to Syracuse Saturday, with Virginia and North Carolina coming to Blacksburg. Pittsburgh (8-16, 3-10) plays at Florida State Wednesday. ------ https://www.espn.com/mens-college-basketball/boxscore/--/gameId/401371139 AP college basketball: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and https://twitter.com/AP--Top25
